    <exercise xml:id="ORCCA-1C2XWyWQZF" license="CC-BY-4.0">
        <statement>
          <p>
            Typically, how many solutions might there be with a quadratic equation?
          </p>
        </statement>
      </exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="ORCCA-Vnxv684mbp" license="CC-BY-4.0">
        <statement>
          <p>
            When you see a <m>\pm</m> sign, as in <m>x=\pm2</m>, is that saying that <m>x</m> is both
            <m>-2</m> and <m>2</m>? Explain.
          </p>
        </statement>
      </exercise>
    <exercise xml:id="ORCCA-ngv4gOiWUq" license="CC-BY-4.0">
